    • getAllFirstLevelByCountry

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> getAllFirstLevelByCountry(Countries country, javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> allFirstLevel)
      The getAllFirstLevelByCountry method creates an observable list of FirstLevelDivision objects. It then searches through a list of all the first level divisions in the database and checks to see if the countryID matches the country parameter's countryID. If a match is found it is added to the list.
      Parameters:
      country - The country whose countryID must be matched.
      allFirstLevel - An observable list of all first level divisions in the database.
      Returns:
      A list of FirstLevelDivision objects whose countryID matches the country parameter's countryID.

    • getAllFirstLevelByCustomer

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> getAllFirstLevelByCustomer(Customer customer, javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> allFirstLevel, javafx.collections.ObservableList<Countries> allCountries)
      The getAllFirstLevelByCustomer creates an observable list of FirstLevelDivision objects. It then searches through a list of all first level divisions in the database for a first level division whose divisionID matches the divisionID of the customer parameter. When a match is found, it searches a list of all countries in the database for a country whose countryID matches the countryID of the found first level division. This matching countryID is saved to an integer. From there, the method again searches the list of all first level divisions, this time searching for a first level division whose countryID matches the saved integer. If a match is found, the first level division is added to the new list.
      Parameters:
      customer - The customer whose divisionID must be matched.
      allFirstLevel - An observable list of all first level divisions in the database.
      allCountries - An observable list of all countries in the database.
      Returns:
      A list of FirstLevelDivision objects whose divisionID matches the customer parameter's divisionID.

    • getCountryName

      public static Countries getCountryName(Customer customer, javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> allFirstLevel, javafx.collections.ObservableList<Countries> allCountries)
      The getCountryName method searches through a list of all first level divisions in the database for a first level division whose divisionID matches the customer parameter's divisionID. When a match is found, the method searches through a list of all countries in the database for a country whose countryID matches the found first level division's countryID. It then returns the matching country.
      Parameters:
      customer - The customer whose divisionID must be matched.
      allFirstLevel - An observable list of all first level divisions in the database.
      allCountries - An observable list of all countries in the database.
      Returns:
      The country whose countryID matches the customer parameter's divisionID via the first level division that matches the customer's divisionID.

    • getFirstLevelName

      public static FirstLevelDivision getFirstLevelName(Customer customer, javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> allFirstLevel)
      The getFirstLevelName method searches through a list of all first level divisions in the database for a first level division whose divisionID matches the customer parameter's divisionID. If a match is found, the first level division is returned.
      Parameters:
      customer - The customer whose divisionID must be matched.
      allFirstLevel - An observable list of all first level divisions in the database.
      Returns:
      The first level division whose divisionID matches the customer parameter's divisionID.
